29#include "nv50.h"
30#include "outp.h"
31
32#include <core/client.h>
33#include <subdev/timer.h>
34
35#include <nvif/class.h>
36#include <nvif/unpack.h>
37
38int
39nv50_dac_power(NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1)
40{
41 struct nvkm_device *device = disp->base.engine.subdev.device;
42 const u32 doff = outp->or * 0x800;
43 union {
44 struct nv50_disp_dac_pwr_v0 v0;
45 } *args = data;
46 u32 stat;
47 int ret;
48
49 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp dac pwr size %d\n", size);
50 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
51 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp dac pwr vers %d state %d data %d "
52 "vsync %d hsync %d\n",
53 args->v0.version, args->v0.state, args->v0.data,
54 args->v0.vsync, args->v0.hsync);
55 stat = 0x00000040 * !args->v0.state;
56 stat |= 0x00000010 * !args->v0.data;
57 stat |= 0x00000004 * !args->v0.vsync;
58 stat |= 0x00000001 * !args->v0.hsync;
59 } else
60 return ret;
61
62 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
63 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a004 + doff) & 0x80000000))
64 break;
65 );
66 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61a004 + doff, 0xc000007f, 0x80000000 | stat);
67 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
68 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a004 + doff) & 0x80000000))
69 break;
70 );
71 return 0;
72}
73
74int
75nv50_dac_sense(NV50_DISP_MTHD_V1)
76{
77 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &disp->base.engine.subdev;
78 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
79 union {
80 struct nv50_disp_dac_load_v0 v0;
81 } *args = data;
82 const u32 doff = outp->or * 0x800;
83 u32 loadval;
84 int ret;
85
86 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp dac load size %d\n", size);
87 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
88 nvif_ioctl(object, "disp dac load vers %d data %08x\n",
89 args->v0.version, args->v0.data);
90 if (args->v0.data & 0xfff00000)
91 return -EINVAL;
92 loadval = args->v0.data;
93 } else
94 return ret;
95
96 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61a004 + doff, 0x807f0000, 0x80150000);
97 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
98 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a004 + doff) & 0x80000000))
99 break;
100 );
101
102 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x61a00c + doff, 0x00100000 | loadval);
103 mdelay(9);
104 udelay(500);
105 loadval = nvkm_mask(device, 0x61a00c + doff, 0xffffffff, 0x00000000);
106
107 nvkm_mask(device, 0x61a004 + doff, 0x807f0000, 0x80550000);
108 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
109 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x61a004 + doff) & 0x80000000))
110 break;
111 );
112
113 nvkm_debug(subdev, "DAC%d sense: %08x\n", outp->or, loadval);
114 if (!(loadval & 0x80000000))
115 return -ETIMEDOUT;
116
117 args->v0.load = (loadval & 0x38000000) >> 27;
118 return 0;
119}

121static const struct nvkm_output_func
122nv50_dac_output_func = {
123};
124
125int
126nv50_dac_output_new(struct nvkm_disp *disp, int index,
127 struct dcb_output *dcbE, struct nvkm_output **poutp)
128{
129 return nvkm_output_new_(&nv50_dac_output_func, disp,
130 index, dcbE, poutp);
131}
